Draw a sphere.

### syntax 

~~~ python
sphere(radius)
~~~

### parameters

radius | radius of sphere

### optional arguments

style    | rendering style: "wireframe" (default) or "solid"
texture  | [Texture](#) object(s)

### examples

#### draw a wireframe sphere


<%= vroom_example_image "rendering", "sphere", "draw-a-wireframe-sphere.png" %>


~~~ python
def display():
   lighting(False)
   color(1.0, 1.0, 1.0)
   sphere(3.0)
~~~

#### draw a solid sphere


<%= vroom_example_image "rendering", "sphere", "draw-a-solid-sphere.png" %>


~~~ python
def display():
   lighting(True)
   material(1.0, 1.0, 1.0)
   sphere(3.0, style='solid')
~~~

#### draw a texture-mapped sphere


<%= vroom_example_image "rendering", "sphere", "draw-a-texture-mapped-sphere.png" %>


~~~ python
def gl_init():
   Global.texture = Texture.from_file('data/globe.png')   

def display():
   lighting(True)
   material(white)
   sphere(3.0, texture=Global.texture)
~~~
